sentences: Doug Raney (August 29, 1956 – May 1, 2016) was an American jazz guitarist.
Raney was born in New York City.
When he was 18, he played at club in New York with pianist Al Haig.
In 1977, he accompanied his father, jazz guitarist Jimmy Raney, in a duo.
They toured Europe, and then Doug Raney moved to Copenhagen, Denmark.
Raney died of heart failure at the age of 59 on May 1, 2016.
